# Virtual Environment

This project uses a Python virtual environment at `./venv`.

- Always activate or reference the venv when running code:
  ```bash
  source venv/bin/activate
  # or use the venv python directly:
  ./venv/bin/python -m pybrowser
  ```
- Install dependencies into the venv, never globally:
  ```bash
  ./venv/bin/pip install -r requirements.txt
  ```
- When running tests or linters, use the venv python:
  ```bash
  ./venv/bin/python -m pytest
  ./venv/bin/python -m ruff check .
  ```
